      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MUSKEE (4) has come from the back row in his two outings off a spell, scoring fresh at Bendigo before working hard and fading here last time. Looks better served by a front row draw so can bounce back. PRETTYBOY HARRY (3) overcame a wide barrier when he scored last week by 4.6 metres at Kilmore. Had put the wiring on the wall with an encouraging minor placing after racing parked the start before. Should enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Has winning claims. OUR MARVELLA NZ (2) enjoys a better draw this week and her best form would measure right up in this line-up. PROHIBITED GRACE (5) was midfield from this barrier last week but had recorded two wins and a second from her previous thee starts so is worth another chance.",
